author: MSNBC.com
title: Biden: ‘This is the time to heal in America’
description: President-elect Joe Biden addresses the nation in a speech in Wilmington, Delaware, and vows to work as hard for those who didn’t vote for him as those who did.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Harris: ‘The road ahead will not be easy, but America is ready’
description: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris speaks to the American people at a victory speech in Wilmington, Delaware.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Biden’s sister says President-elect Biden is an ‘optimist,’ ready for job ahead
description: NBC News’ Mike Memoli says those close to President-elect Joe Biden say he’s ready for the job and proud of the history Vice President-elect Kamala Harris is making.
source.name: MSNBC

title: Engel: World reacted to Biden win like U.S. overthrew a dictator
description: NBC News Chief Foreign Correspondent Richard Engel joins to share reaction to Joe Biden's defeat of Donald Trump from U.S. allies around the globe.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Biden campaign: Constitution doesn't require Trump to concede
description: Biden-Harris Senior Adviser Symone Sanders joins to discuss whether there has been any communications between the Biden Camp and the Trump White House about the upcoming transition.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Jon Meacham: Biden win is a reminder of America's possibility
description: Pulitzer Prize-winning presidential biographer Jon Meacham explains what he believes the transition from a Trump White House to a Biden White House will mean for America.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Kamala Harris takes her place in history as vice president-elect
description: Errin Haines, editor-at-large for The 19th, reacts to the historic candidacy and win of Kamala Harris who is poised to reach the highest office ever obtained by a woman in America.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Clyburn, who gave critical endorsement, reacts to Biden win
description: Rep. James Clyburn, who delivered a shot to the arm of the Biden campaign in February, joins to react to Joe Biden's win against Donald Trump.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Does democracy grow back like the limb of a starfish?
description: Michael Steele, fmr. RNC Chairman who endorsed Joe Biden for president, reacts to the Biden's win and victory speech to the nation.
source.name: MSNBC

title: Rep Ilhan Omar: 'My life is an example of what can happen when people are willing to give you a chance'

author: MSNBC.com
title: Nikole Hannah-Jones: 'Black people believed in our founding ideals even when our founders did not'
description: Pulitzer Prize-winning New York Times reporter Nikole Hannah-Jones discusses the role of Black voters in the 2020 election and how there is still more work to be done. She says, “I think it’s OK to take a moment and feel some joy about what just happened, but…

title: Missouri's first Black Congresswoman: “I’ve slept in my car… I don’t want that for anyone else.”

title: Women of color leaders on historic import of VP-Elect Harris
description: Kamala Harris as America’s vice president-elect is celebrated as a win for all, as she will be the first woman, first person of color, and first child of immigrants to become the vice president of the United States. Ari Melber and a panel of women of color le…

author: MSNBC.com
title: Doctor praises Biden presidency as key in COVID-19 fight
description: President-Elect Joe Biden’s Covid-19 task force announcement is coming on Monday. The coming Biden presidency is praised as a game changer in the COVID-19 fight by Dr. Bernard Ashby.

title: Presidential historian warns ‘maybe Trump will never concede’
description: Donald Trump might never concede according to reports, despite every other president in recent history conceding gracefully, presidential historian Michael Beschloss warns.

title: Crowds gather for second day at Black Lives Matter Plaza after Biden victory projected
description: Crowds gathered at Black Lives Matter Plaza in Washington, D.C., for a second day to celebrate the Biden-Harris victory projected. NBC News’ Amanda Golden spoke with a group of women who said they came out to celebrate history.
